[
    {
        "content": "<p>I just looked a bit on Allocating a Box with a flag. They way I would like to do is only possible when changing the alloc crate. as this does not compile:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// Box extension Proiding functions to pass GFP flags to the allocator.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BoxAllocFlagExt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span>: <span class=\"nc\">FlagAllocator</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Allocate uninit box with flags.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">try_new_uninit_flag_in</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span>: <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">gfp_t</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alloc</span>: <span class=\"nc\">A</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">mem</span>::<span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Allocated uninit box with flags on Global Allocator.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">try_new_uninit_flag</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span>: <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">gfp_t</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">mem</span>::<span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">where</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">A</span>: <span class=\"nc\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">Global</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_new_uninit_flag_in</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">Global</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 288493679,
        "sender_full_name": "Fiona Behrens",
        "timestamp": 1657009178
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"498029\">@Andreas Hindborg</span> Maybe take a look at this.<br>\n I guess we could provide two ext traits, but also not that nice</p>",
        "id": 288495062,
        "sender_full_name": "Fiona Behrens",
        "timestamp": 1657010043
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Created a pr for that like this for now: <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/pull/811\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/pull/811</a></p>",
        "id": 288500805,
        "sender_full_name": "Fiona Behrens",
        "timestamp": 1657013288
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"412307\">Finn Behrens</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291566-Library/topic/FlagAllocator/near/288493679\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I just looked a bit on Allocating a Box with a flag. They way I would like to do is only possible when changing the alloc crate. as this does not compile:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// Box extension Proiding functions to pass GFP flags to the allocator.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BoxAllocFlagExt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span>: <span class=\"nc\">FlagAllocator</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Allocate uninit box with flags.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">try_new_uninit_flag_in</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span>: <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">gfp_t</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alloc</span>: <span class=\"nc\">A</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">mem</span>::<span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Allocated uninit box with flags on Global Allocator.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">try_new_uninit_flag</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span>: <span class=\"nc\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">gfp_t</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">mem</span>::<span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">where</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">A</span>: <span class=\"nc\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">Global</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_new_uninit_flag_in</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">Global</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This still change the type of the box and the box would have to be freed with the <code>FlagAllocator</code>. But it would be fine to free with the default allocator.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BoxExt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span>: <span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">try_new_atomic</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span>: <span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BoxExt</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">try_new_atomic</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span>: <span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">layout</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">Layout</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span>::<span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">mem</span>::<span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">();</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span>::<span class=\"n\">ALLOCATOR_ATOMIC</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">allocate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">layout</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">();</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">boxed</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">MaybeUninit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">from_raw_in</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">alloc</span>::<span class=\"n\">Global</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">boxed</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_mut_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">boxed</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">assume_init</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>With this approach we could use whatever allocation function we want and still free with the global allocator without changing the type of the box. This is only atomic, but we could add a param for the flag.</p>",
        "id": 288503213,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1657014460
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We don't want to expose <code>bindings::gfp_t</code> -- we actually want to make <code>bindings</code> private</p>",
