    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"412307\">@Finn Behrens</span>  How about keeping the <code>FlagAllocator</code> form your PR and use that in the <code>BoxExt::try_new_atomic()</code>. Not sure about the naming of the extension trait. It seems people favor just adding <code>Ext</code> to the identifier, but it does not say much about the reason for the extension.</p>",
        "id": 288504648,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1657015214
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The one thing I dislike about that is the dependency on ALLOCATOR_ATOMIC. but ok. Can rebase my FlagAllocator (as private trait) on top of just the try_new_atomic function.</p>",
